[YouTube](/wiki/YouTube "YouTube") is an American video-sharing website
headquartered in [San Bruno, California](/wiki/San_Bruno,_California "San
Bruno, California"). Since its establishment in 2005, the website has featured
a "most viewed" section, which lists the most viewed videos on the site.
Although the most viewed videos were initially viral videos, such as
_[Evolution of Dance](/wiki/Evolution_of_Dance "Evolution of Dance")_ and
_[Charlie Bit My Finger](/wiki/Charlie_Bit_My_Finger "Charlie Bit My Finger")_
, the most viewed videos were increasingly related to [music
videos](/wiki/Music_videos "Music videos"). In fact, since [Lady
Gaga](/wiki/Lady_Gaga "Lady Gaga")'s "[Bad Romance](/wiki/Bad_Romance "Bad
Romance")", every video that has reached the top of the "most viewed YouTube
videos" list has been a music video. Although the most viewed videos are no
longer listed on the site, reaching the top of the list is still considered a
tremendous feat.

By June 21, 2015, only two videos, "[Gangnam
Style](/wiki/Gangnam_Style_\(music_video\) "Gangnam Style \(music video\)")"
and "[Baby](/wiki/Baby_\(Justin_Bieber_song\)#Music_video "Baby \(Justin
Bieber song\)")", had exceeded one billion views. However, three and a half
months later, on October 7, ten videos had done so.[1] As of November 2017, 86
videos on the list have exceeded one billion views, with 18 of them exceeding
two billion views; three of which exceed three billion views and one of which
exceeds four billion views. "[Despacito](/wiki/Despacito "Despacito")" became
the first video to reach three billion views on August 4, 2017, followed by
"[See You Again](/wiki/See_You_Again "See You Again")" on August 6, 2017, and
then on November 25, 2017, "[Gangnam Style](/wiki/Gangnam_Style "Gangnam
Style")" became the third video to hit three billion views.[2][3][4]
"Despacito" also became the first video to reach four billion views on October
11, 2017.[5]

As of November 2017, the five fastest videos to reach the one billion view
mark are "[Hello](/wiki/Hello_\(Adele_song\)#Music_video "Hello \(Adele
song\)")" (87 days), "[Despacito](/wiki/Despacito#Music_video "Despacito")"
(96 days), "[Shape of You](/wiki/Shape_of_You#Music_video "Shape of You")" (97
days), "[Mi
Gente](/wiki/Mi_Gente_\(J_Balvin_and_Willy_William_song\)#Music_video "Mi
Gente \(J Balvin and Willy William song\)")" (102 days) and
"[Sorry](/wiki/Sorry_\(Justin_Bieber_song\)#Music_video "Sorry \(Justin Bieber
song\)")" (136 days).[6]

The five fastest videos to reach two billion views are "Despacito" (154 days),
"Shape of You" (187 days), "Sorry" (394 days), "[See You
Again](/wiki/See_You_Again#Music_video "See You Again")" (515 days) and
"Hello" (619 days).[7]

As of November 2017, [Justin Bieber](/wiki/Justin_Bieber "Justin Bieber") and
[Katy Perry](/wiki/Katy_Perry "Katy Perry") each have four videos exceeding
one billion views, while [Taylor Swift](/wiki/Taylor_Swift "Taylor Swift"),
[Calvin Harris](/wiki/Calvin_Harris "Calvin Harris"), [Shakira](/wiki/Shakira
"Shakira"), [Ariana Grande](/wiki/Ariana_Grande "Ariana Grande") and [Bruno
Mars](/wiki/Bruno_Mars "Bruno Mars") each have three, and [Fifth
Harmony](/wiki/Fifth_Harmony "Fifth Harmony"), [Psy](/wiki/Psy "Psy"),
[Adele](/wiki/Adele "Adele"), [Ellie Goulding](/wiki/Ellie_Goulding "Ellie
Goulding"), [The Weeknd](/wiki/The_Weeknd "The Weeknd"), [Ed
Sheeran](/wiki/Ed_Sheeran "Ed Sheeran"), [Nicky Jam](/wiki/Nicky_Jam "Nicky
Jam"), [Eminem](/wiki/Eminem "Eminem"), [Maluma](/wiki/Maluma_\(singer\)
"Maluma \(singer\)"), [J Balvin](/wiki/J_Balvin "J Balvin") and [Ricky
Martin](/wiki/Ricky_Martin "Ricky Martin") each have two. Swift and Perry are
the only artists to have two videos exceeding two billion views.
